David is an undergraduate student at Harvard studying Computer Science. He has a background in applying Artificial Intelligence towards Drug Discovery, working at the San Diego Supercomputer Center (SDSC) and Takeda Pharmaceuticals. He's published his work at SDSC in two papers: one on using AI transfer-learning techniques to study the receptor of advanced glycation endproducts for treatment of Alzheimer's, and another on using docking and pharmacophore techniques to study the SARS-CoV-2 main protease. At Takeda, he worked to characterize the applicability domain and robustness of machine learning models, as well as the initial development of a de novo molecular design tool.
